  "title": "Resident Technical Officer (RTO) | Cable Work (HV/EHV/HT/MW)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Resident Technical Officer</strong></u></p><p><strong>$4,000 – $6,800 per month</strong><br /><strong>6 days/ week</strong><br /><strong>Day & Night Shift/ working hour (Only discuss during interview session with hiring manager)</strong><br /><strong>6-month contract (with potential to convert to permanent based on performance)</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Good co-ordination skills and good technical knowledge of M&E systems/ equipment, including security systems.</li><li>To carry out regular site supervision and inspection of the works/materials including any off-site production as instructed by the consultant team so as to ensure that mechanical and electrical works, including security systems, are constructed to required quality, accuracy and workmanship.</li><li>To monitor work in progress in accordance to Approved Master Schedules with breakdown to Monthly, Weekly and Daily programmes.</li><li>To assist the RE on daily, weekly and monthly reports of site progress as per contractor’s approved program, activities, issues and resolutions.</li><li>To check and verify reports, variaations and progress claims submitted by contractors, including as built quantity for the variations.</li><li>To undertake any other duties related to the project as and when instructed by the SO and RE.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>M&E or Electrical Background.</li><li>Relevant experience in cable works / utilities road works.</li></ul><p><strong>Added Value:</strong></p><ul><li>Acquire Safety @ SPPG / Project Safety Management (PSM) by SP</li><li>Accredited with IES/ACES with a valid Resident Technical Officer Practicing Certificate.</li><li>Have own transport (travelling to remote areas)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Chin Racheal (R25157940)</p><p>Business Edge Personnel Services Pte Ltd (96C4864)</p>",
